.TH REDB 8 "May 2023" "refsprogs @VERSION@"
.SH NAME
redb \- Print debugging information for an ReFS volume
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B redb
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIdevice\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B redb
will print debugging information an ReFS volume. When no options are specified,
all reachable trees on the volume will be printed to stdout.

Run
.B redb
without arguments for a full list of options.
.SH OPTIONS
Below is a summary of all the options that
.B redb
accepts.  Nearly all options have two equivalent names.  The short name is
preceded by
.B \-
and the long name is preceded by
.BR \-\- .
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-scan\fR
Scan device for metadata signatures and print found signatures to stdout.
.SH BUGS
There are no known problems with
.BR redb .
If you find a bug, then please report it to the refsprogs bug tracker on github:
https://github.com/unsound/refsprogs/issues
.hy
.SH AUTHORS
.B redb
was written by Erik Larsson
.SH AVAILABILITY
.B redb
is part of the
.B refsprogs
package.
.hy
.SH SEE ALSO
